3.00	Santons	Santon (figurine)	Santons (Provençal: "santoun," or "little saint") are small (2.5–15 cm.) hand-painted, terracotta nativity scene figurines produced in the Provence region of southeastern France. In a traditional Provençal crèche, there are 55 individual figures representing various characters from Provençal village life such as the scissors grinder, the fishwife, the blind man, and the chestnut seller.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Santon_mara%C3%AEcher.jpg/220px-Santon_mara%C3%AEcher.jpg
